<h1>Gnomonic Butterfly Map</h1>
<div id="map"></div>

<div class="wrapper">
  <p>Available as <code>d3.geo.polyhedron.butterfly</code> in the <a href="http://github.com/d3/d3-plugins/tree/master/geo/polyhedron">geo.polyhedron D3 plugin</a>.
  <p>The <a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/GnomonicProjection.html">gnomonic projection</a> is used in the butterfly map above.
  This conveniently projects <a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/GreatCircle.html">great circle</a> segments as straight lines, hence it is useful for polyhedral projections in general.
</div>

<script src="../../d3.min.js?3.0.2"></script>
<script src="../d3.geo.projection.min.js"></script>
<script src="../d3.geo.polyhedron.js"></script>
<script src="../maps.js"></script>
<script src="../topojson.min.js?1.0.0pre"></script>
<script>

var projection = d3.geo.polyhedron.butterfly().scale(110).center([0, 45]);

d3.select("#map").call(canvasMap().projection(projection));

</script>
